  "description": "Blockchain-inspired patterns (event sourcing, DocSync), MDD, RAD, CQRS, and EDA as the technical methodology behind Powerhouse.",
  "orientation": "Powerhouse's development methodology draws from blockchain principles while diverging where global consensus is impractical. Event sourcing provides immutable audit trails. DocSync enables P2P synchronization without server dependency. Local-first workflows prioritize contributor efficiency over global coordination. On top of this, Model-Driven Development uses abstract models as shared blueprints across teams, RAD accelerates iteration through code generation and pre-built frameworks, CQRS separates reads from writes for independent scaling, and EDA decouples components so validation, notifications, and analytics run in parallel. These approaches combine to make Powerhouse systems responsive, auditable, and scalable without the performance bottlenecks of on-chain consensus.",
